text: Senate agrees to tax hike package 23-18 and it goes to Guv. It does not change for now personal income tax rates. The Legislature is set to adjourn at noon.
author: newsguy44

text: Final minutes of legislative session see Senate debating compromise tax hike bill approved by House. The package would raise $65 to $70 million annually, says Sen. Clemente Sanchez, down from original $300 million. Session adjourns at noon. http://joemonahan.com
author: newsguy44

text: Final night of ‘19 legislative session done. Senate adjourned until 8:30 am. House comes back at 7:45.  Major outstanding issue of session is tax hike bill. All other major issues have been put to bed. Adjournment @ noon today.  http://joemonahan.com
author: newsguy44

text: House adjourned. Back at 7:45 am. Senate finishing on final night of Session ‘19. Legalized pot didn’t make it but decriminalization passes and goes to Guv. Possession of 1/2 ounce civil violation punishable by small fine. Session ends at noon today. http://joemonahan.com
author: newsguy44

text: 11 o’clock in the mountain west and it’s political junkie action @NM Legislature. In session tonite with noon adjournment tomorrow. Tax bill remains last major point of contention. Ethics commission being debated in House. Looks like a go as @DaymonforNMHD23 presents compromise.
author: newsguy44
